Description: Logitech G510/G510s keyboard daemon for Linux
 Userspace driver daemon for the Logitech G510 and G510s gaming keyboards.
 .
 Features:
  - G1-G18 macro keys with M1/M2/M3 bank switching
  - MR macro record mode (records key sequences on the fly)
  - RGB backlight control (via kernel sysfs or USB HID)
  - LCD GamePanel rendering (clock, sysinfo, now-playing, custom)
  - Media keys, volume wheel, mute/mic-mute
  - G510s: headphone/mic mute LEDs, game-mode key
  - Auto model detection (G510 vs G510s)
  - JSON profile system with D-Bus interface
 .
 Requires the hid-lg-g15 kernel module (mainline since Linux 5.5).

Package: g510-gui
Architecture: all
Depends:
 ${python3:Depends},
 ${misc:Depends},
 g510-daemon (= ${binary:Version}),
 python3-gi,
 gir1.2-gtk-3.0,
 python3-dbus
Description: GTK3 control panel for the Logitech G510/G510s keyboard
 Graphical configuration tool for the G510/G510s keyboard daemon.
 Designed for LXQt and other X11 desktop environments.
 .
 Features:
  - Macro editor (per G-key, per M-bank)
  - RGB colour picker with live preview
  - LCD screen selector with in-app preview
  - Profile manager (create, delete, import, export)
  - Live bank indicator and game-mode status
